<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes, I think this is an excellent - if difficult - read. The subject matter can be at times disturbing, eg descriptions of a 19th century British &apos;asy<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes, I think this is an excellent - if difficult - read. The subject matter can be at times disturbing, eg descriptions of a 19th century British 'asylum' for the insane, originally envisioned as a haven for the mentally ill. But aside from the seriousness of the theme (psychiatry), the novel is well-written, character development is good, and you learn a lot, conveyed through the eyes of the main character. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
